  "texts": [
    "The results of Fig. 6c showing abrogation of TMZ-induced (C>A, C>G, T>A, T>C and T>G) SNVs in RAD18 -/-cells suggest that RAD18 is responsible for error-prone bypass of N 7 mG and N 3 mA lesions.",
    "In MMRdeficient MLH1 -/-cells, the SNV (C>T) was TMZ-inducible in both RAD18 +/+ and RAD18 -/-genetic backgrounds (Fig. 6d).",
    "However, unlike the MLH1 +/+ cells, the other five less abundant SNVs were not induced by TMZ in an MLH1 -/-background (Fig. 6d).",
    "Therefore RAD18-mediated error-prone bypass of N 7 mG and N 3 mA lesions is MMR-dependent.",
    "We also determined the impact of RAD18 and MLH1 on TMZinduced COSMIC \"mutation signatures\"."
  ],
